[gd_resource type="TileSet" load_steps=5 format=3 uid="uid://b0embergrave_s1yard_tileset"]

; S1 cloister-YARD TileSet — ticket 86ca5erzk (S1-YARD T4; Uma s1-cloister-yard.md §3).
; The open-air YARD floor + finer perimeter-brick, distinct from the interior-hall
; `s1_cloister.tres` (sandstone flagstone). Two atlas sources, 32px tiles:
;   Source 0 = floor_cobble.png   → CLEAN GREY cobblestone yard ground, NO baked
;                vegetation (generator `tools/gen_s1_cobble_floor.py`, LOCKED tone =
;                lighter warm-neutral GREY + fine varied-size stones the Sponsor LOVED).
;                Sponsor approval lock 2026-06-07: "drop the grass in the cobblestone" —
;                ALL moss/green/grass stripped from the tile (dirt was cut earlier).
;                Vegetation returns LATER as a deliberate decoration LAYER, not baked in.
;                MULTI-VARIANT atlas: 768x128 = 24x4 cells = SIX 4x4 variant-blocks (each
;                a distinct 384px source downsampled to 128px; variant v = cols
;                [v*4 .. v*4+3]). The painter (S1YardChunk._paint_floor) scatters the 6
;                variants per 4-tile block with a NON-TILING hash so adjacent yard blocks
;                differ and no block-cluster repeats (PR #424 Sponsor repeat-stamp fix;
;                Uma §3.4 multi-variant set). Each variant's STONES stay toroidally
;                seamless internally; variation is at the block level.
;   Source 1 = wall_cloister_fine.png → finer-brick perimeter (T2; Sponsor flagged the
;                old 128px running-bond bricks as oversized vs the finer cobble). Brick
;                pitch shrunk ~2x (downsample-to-64 + 2x2 retile) so bricks read ~6
;                courses, harmonizing with the cobble. 128x128 = 4x4 atlas, period 4.
;   Source 2 = floor_sandstone.png → warm-sandstone FLAGSTONE, REUSED as the worn
;                processional SLAB-PATH material (S1-YARD T8, Uma s1-yard-ground-
;                composition.md §2.1: the SET-ASIDE base material becomes the path
;                material — large flat cut stones, warmer + larger-stone than the cool
;                cobble = the "warm path through cool field" wayfinding read, PL-PATH-01/02).
;                64x64 = 2x2 atlas, period 2. The S1YardChunk painter lays these as
;                RIBBONS (spine + building-links + well-apron) into the SlabPaths layer
;                AND erases the cobble cell beneath (one tile-class per cell at z=0 — no
;                stacked-z, no z-fight per html5-export.md §Z-index + the T8 AC9 rule).
; Tile size 32px matches LevelChunkDef.tile_size_px=32.
; Textures referenced by path (project default_texture_filter=0 = Nearest → pixel crisp);
; .import files gitignored, regenerated by headless Godot on first import.
; Palette-locked to S1_YARD_FLOOR_DOCTRINE (s1-cloister-yard.md §3.2, sub-1.0 verified)
; inside the PNG itself — the .tres only declares geometry, never colour.

[ext_resource type="Texture2D" path="res://assets/tilesets/s1_cloister/floor_cobble.png" id="1_cobble"]
[ext_resource type="Texture2D" path="res://assets/tilesets/s1_cloister/wall_cloister_fine.png" id="2_wall_fine"]
[ext_resource type="Texture2D" path="res://assets/tilesets/s1_cloister/floor_sandstone.png" id="3_slab"]

